<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>Trade Failed</title>
  <style>
    body { margin: 0; padding: 0; font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif; background-color: #f8fafc; }
    .container { max-width: 600px; margin: 0 auto; background-color: #ffffff; border-radius: 8px; overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 4px 6px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); }
    .header { background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ef4444 0%, #dc2626 100%); color: white; padding: 30px; text-align: center; }
    .content { padding: 30px; }
    .error-box { background-color: #fee2e2; padding: 20px; border-radius: 6px; margin: 15px 0; border-left: 4px solid #ef4444; }
    .info-box { background-color: #f0f9ff; padding: 20px; border-radius: 6px; margin: 15px 0; border-left: 4px solid #3b82f6; }
    .footer { background-color: #f8fafc; padding: 20px; text-align: center; color: #6b7280; font-size: 14px; }
    .code { background-color: #f3f4f6; padding: 8px; border-radius: 4px; font-family: monospace; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <div class="header">
      <h1>⚠️ Trade Failed</h1>
      <p>Your automated trade could not be executed</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="content">
      <h2>Hello <%= @user.full_name || @user.email %>! 🛠️</h2>
      
      <p>We encountered an issue while trying to execute your automated trade for <strong><%= @signal&.symbol || 'Unknown' %></strong>.</p>
      
      <div class="error-box">
        <h3>❌ Error Details:</h3>
        <p><strong>Error:</strong> <span class="code"><%= @error_message %></span></p>
        <% if @signal %>
        <p><strong>Signal:</strong> <%= @signal.symbol %> <%= @signal.side %></p>
        <p><strong>Entry Price:</strong> $<%= number_with_delimiter(@signal.entry_price, delimiter: ',') %></p>
        <p><strong>Channel:</strong> <%= @signal.channel.name %></p>
        <% end %>
      </div>
      
      <div class="info-box">
        <h3>🔧 Common Solutions:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Insufficient Balance:</strong> Ensure you have enough USDT in your Binance account</li>
          <li><strong>API Key Issues:</strong> Verify your Binance API keys are valid and have trading permissions</li>
          <li><strong>Symbol Problems:</strong> Check if the trading pair is available on Binance</li>
          <li><strong>Network Issues:</strong> Temporary connectivity problems - trade will be retried</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <div class="info-box">
        <h3>🚀 Next Steps:</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Check your Binance account balance and API key status</li>
          <li>Review your trading settings in the Tramate dashboard</li>
          <li>Contact support if the issue persists</li>
          <li>Future signals will continue to be processed automatically</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      
      <p><strong>No Action Required:</strong> Your automated trading system will continue monitoring for new signals. If this was a temporary issue, subsequent trades should work normally.</p>
      
      <p>Need help? Contact our support team with this error message for quick assistance.</p>
      
      <p>Best regards,<br>
      The Tramate Team 🎯</p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="footer">
      <p>Error occurred at <%= Time.current.strftime("%B %d, %Y at %I:%M %p %Z") %></p>
      <p>© 2024 Tramate. All rights reserved.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html> 